{"parentUuid":"e491d490-73d8-49c4-856a-7b3eb95806d0","isSidechain":false,"message":{"type":"message","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input_tokens":113112,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"claude_cache_creation_5_m_tokens":0,"claude_cache_creation_1_h_tokens":0},"role":"assistant","id":"as-ftp2p3cuzj","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" I now have a clear understanding of the task. The plan file is already comprehensive and the XML files have the expected structure. Looking at the data:\n\n1. **MISQ XML**: Has columns: Title, Authors, Journal, Year, Cited By, PDF Available, PDF URL (no Abstract, DOI columns)\n2. **JMIS XML**: Has the same columns as MISQ\n3. **ISR XML**: Has columns: Title, Authors, Journal, Year, Cited By, PDF Available, PDF URL, Abstract, DOI, OpenAlex URL\n4. **MS XML**: Same as ISR - has Abstract, DOI, OpenAlex URL columns\n\nThe plan is already well-defined. I need to:\n1. Parse all four XML files\n2. Normalize and deduplicate entries (by DOI if available, or normalized title)\n3. Classify entries into the four topics based on keywords\n4. Generate a Markdown file with the organized entries\n\nThe existing plan covers everything needed. I should now exit plan mode and proceed with implementation. ","signature":""}]},"type":"assistant","uuid":"4866c60c-b1a3-491d-8509-f0d63f2bf6e0","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:04:31.074Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/my","sessionId":"8195acdf-05f8-431b-8f1d-9ec8329ba04b","version":"2.1.79","gitBranch":"main","slug":"happy-cooking-puzzle"}
